(
Figures 18–21
)

Animal:
Head (
Fig. 19F
) black, usually an unpigmented stripe across snout; tentacle pale around eye and across base, with two short longitudinal grey to black stripes up to half tentacle length (often fused to give a grey or black basal band) and usually a black dot at tip; sides of foot with grey or black blotches. Opercular ratio 0.36–0.40. Penis (Fig. A–E, G): filament 0.6–0.7 total length of penis, with annular wrinkles for most of its length (so not clearly differentiated from wrinkled base), sperm groove ends at about two-thirds length of filament, where its lips are broadened, filament extends distally in a smooth oblique wedge-shape; mamilliform gland approximately half size of penial glandular disc, borne together on projection of base; penis unpigmented. Euspermatozoa 53–70 µm; paraspermatozoa (
Fig. 19I, J
) containing 1–2 parallel-sided (occasionally slightly fusiform) rod-pieces 16–29 µm (exceptionally to 49 µm), with rounded ends, usually projecting slightly from cell, which is packed with round granules. Pallial oviduct (
Fig. 19H
): copulatory bursa separates at posterior end of straight section and extends back almost to albumen gland. Spawn (
Fig. 19K
): a large pelagic capsule 660–720 µm diameter by 425–440 µm high, with broad peripheral skirt bearing oblique striations overhanging base, dome-shaped upper half sculptured by 4 concentric rings, containing single ovum 135–160 µm diameter (
Lewis 1960
: 
Barbados
; 
Borkowski 1971
: Florida).

Radula (
Fig. 20
):

Relative radula length 4.54–9.60. Rachidian: length/width 2.26–6.0, sometimes narrow (
Fig. 20E, G
); tip of major cusp pointed. Lateral and inner marginal: 4 cusps, tip of major cusp rounded; when rachidian is narrow the major cusp of both lateral and inner marginal is enlarged and more pointed, innermost and outermost cusp of each tooth are then vestigial or absent (
Fig. 20E, G
). Outer marginal: normal form with 6 cusps, but narrowed to a rod with 5 cusps in form with narrow rachidian (
Fig. 20G
).

Range ( Fig. 21 ):
On islands throughout the Caribbean Sea , Bahamas , E Florida , rare in Bermuda and Gulf of Mexico . Range limits: Boca Chica Key , Florida ( USNM 820421 )
